Rating: 4
I made this recipe a couple days back and plan on making more! It really is a tasty, creamy, guilt-free dessert. I used about half the amount of sugar, and instead of the dried mango and coconut topping, I mixed in some spiced pears and cranberries (I had filling left over from this recipe http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/foo d/views/Pear-Cranberry-Turnovers- 362951). I realize what I made is quite a deviation from the original recipe, and I'll re-review after making a truer version if I find it disappointing.

